gm installer detail (bin/install.js, gm-method): canonical installer, no npx skills library, no marketplace. Copies skills/gm into <home>/.claude/skills/gm/ (personal) or .claude/skills/gm/ (--project); dir name IS the /command. Non-interactive (-y/--yes or non-TTY) SETS four Claude Code settings (autoCompactEnabled:true, autoCompactWindow:380000 -- an ABSOLUTE token count = 38% of 1M, not a percentage -- effortLevel:'low', alwaysThinkingEnabled:false) and explains the revert; interactive OFFERS them. The reasoning-in-code framing it prints is load-bearing: the LLM still thinks, it tests its thoughts in code (execution as reasoning). test.js checkRenameAndInstaller() is the structural guard (asserts no skills/gm-skill, package id stays gm-skill, installer lands the skill + writes the four keys into an isolated temp HOME).